    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Coopers' tools for ploughing the groove or channel in cask staves,  for the attachment of the barrel heads; the channels themselves are also called "crozes." The tools may be mounted with a channel-cutting tooth.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
